message.content:
We start by extracting the key numbers from the End_amount columns in the balance sheet and cash flow:

1. From the balance sheet:
 • Total Current Assets = 9,122,854.19  
 • Inventory = 7,869,940.00  
 • Total Current Liabilities = 3,389,719.66  
 • Total Assets = 19,501,451.49  
 • Total Owner's Equity = 16,111,731.83  
  • Total Liabilities = Total Assets – Owner's Equity  
    = 19,501,451.49 – 16,111,731.83  
    = 3,389,719.66

2. From the cash flow statement:
 • Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –4,504,752.68

Now, we compute each ratio:

A. Current Ratio  
 Formula: Current Assets / Current Liabilities  
 Calculation: 9,122,854.19 / 3,389,719.66 ≈ 2.69

B. Quick Ratio  
 Formula: (Current Assets – Inventory) / Current Liabilities  
 First, calculate quick assets:  
  = 9,122,854.19 – 7,869,940.00  
  = 1,252,914.19  
 Then, Quick Ratio:  
  = 1,252,914.19 / 3,389,719.66 ≈ 0.37

C. Debt to Asset Ratio  
 Formula: Total Liabilities / Total Assets  
 Calculation: 3,389,719.66 / 19,501,451.49 ≈ 0.17

D. Debt to Equity Ratio  
 Formula: Total Liabilities / Total Owner's Equity  
 Calculation: 3,389,719.66 / 16,111,731.83 ≈ 0.21

E. Cash Flow to Debt Ratio  
 Formula: Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Liabilities  
 Calculation: –4,504,752.68 / 3,389,719.66 ≈ –1.33

Thus, our solution in the required JSON format is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Current Ratio": "2.69",
    "Quick Ratio": "0.37",
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.17",
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.21",
    "Cash Flow to Debt Ratio": "-1.33"
  }
}
